  "text": "For initiatives that involve multi-institutional collaboration, there are assorted data harmonization processes in place. For example, the EU-ADR Alliance uses databases having different characteristics, so the Unified Medical Language System (UMLS) is used to map different terminologies [CITATION_1] . The PRISM (in the US Mini-Sentinel) chose to use the HL7 system and applied this to acquire standardized information from different data partners.",
